How to Install

|---- For more details, please see the video at: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OUp79vD4f0Q ----|

- run gparted from the start menu (user midfingr password guest)
alternative:
-------- terminal method --------
- open a terminal and type: su
- type: fidsk
- create the partitions as needed.
- make your file system(s) i.e. mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda1
-----------------------------------

- mount the partition(s) i.e. mount /dev/sda1 /mnt
- type: ame
** this will take a while; when done you should be in a chroot environment
- type: mkinitcpio -p linux
- type: grub-install /dev/sda
- type: up-grub
- type: exit
- type: umount /mnt -R

reboot

